result.name: Sake Bar Ginn

reviews.text: This is my favourite sake place in HK. Been a regular since 2013. The bar has great food and great selection of sake. Last but not for least, an amazing owner.
Nice quiet place for some distinctive sake and small snacks. Good cold Siva with dried seaweed flakes and good mini sardines crackers. Feels like in a Japanese isakaya back in Osaka.

Great little hidden sake bar in the LKF area. They have a rather extensive range of Artisanal craft sakes. Food quality was good too. Great service and they are most helpful if you ever need help with choosing a sake to pair with your food. If you love good non commercial sakes, this is the place to be!
Very delicious dishes with a wide range of Sake selection in terms of price and quality
Great service, lovely sake. Location could ve better. The heart of LKF is a little too loud.
